Package model

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Map
    I think the ability to add different maps is an example of a strategy pattern In this case, the way we generate maps can benefit from variants of an algorithm.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Ball
    The ball is actually a rectangle.
    Block
    Rectangles are displayed or not displayed depending on that rectangle's number of lives.
    Model
    Handles the calculation of all the physics and stores objects which it manipulates.
    Player
    Player is the paddle.
    Rect
    Ball, Player, and bricks are all things that can be built using fillRect, so I'm using these to keep track of measurement data.
